# Git & GitHub Workflow

No Jira â€” track work in **GitHub Issues** and the repo **Project board**. OpenSpec remains the spec source of truth; issues provide cross-links and audit history.

## Branches

- **`master`** â€” stable / release-ready. **Maintainer only:** merge from `dev`; no direct contributor PRs.
- **`dev`** â€” integration branch. **All contributor PRs target `dev`.**
- **Feature branches** â€” one branch per OpenSpec change or fix, cut from `dev`:
  - `feat/<change-name>` â€” new capability (`/apply`)
  - `fix/<topic>` â€” bug fixes
  - `chore/<topic>` â€” CI, docs, tooling
- **Fork workflow:** contributors fork the repo, branch from `dev`, PR back to `dev`. See [CONTRIBUTING.md](../CONTRIBUTING.md).
- Create the branch at `/apply` (or before, for chores). Push early; open a **draft PR** linked to the issue.

## Issues

- Create or reference a GitHub Issue **before** `/apply` when the work is non-trivial.
- Title format: `[<change-name>] Short description`.
- Issue body MUST include:
  - Link to `openspec/changes/<change-name>/` (or note that `/enrich-us` is needed)
  - Acceptance criteria (copy from `user-story.md` or task list)
  - Target branch name
- Labels: `change`, `area:*`, `priority:*` as applicable.
- **Comments:** when status changes, post `**Status:**`, `**Branch:**`, `**Notes:**` on the issue (see `.github/PROJECT.md`).
- Close the issue in the PR description (`Closes #N`) when merging after `/archive`.

## Project board

- Board: **<your-project>** â€” <project-board-url>
- Setup guide: [`.github/PROJECT.md`](../.github/PROJECT.md)

### Status (update on every stage change)

| Status | SPECBOOT stage |
|--------|----------------|
| Backlog | `/enrich-us` or `/propose` not started |
| Ready | Scoped; proposal done or N/A; pick up next |
| In progress | branch + `/apply` |
| In review | PR open; `/verify` + `/code-review` |
| Done | merged to `dev` (contributors) or `master` (release); `/archive` complete |

Move the card on the board **and** leave a brief issue comment (status, branch, next step).

### Milestones

- **v0.1 â€” Foundation** â€” initial scaffold, CI bootstrap, governance
- **v0.2 â€” Fixes & tooling** â€” bugs, CI, docs chores
- **Future** â€” needs `/propose` before `/apply`

Assign milestone at issue creation. Use the **By milestone** project view to plan releases.

### Views

Create in the project UI (see `.github/PROJECT.md`): **Board** (group by Status), **Ready queue**, **By milestone**, **In review**.

## Pull requests

- **Contributors:** target `dev`.
- **Maintainer release:** `dev` â†’ `master` when integrating a release.
- Title: same as issue or `[change-name] summary`.
- Body: `Closes #N`, summary, test plan, link to `testing-report.md` (use [PR template](../.github/pull_request_template.md)).
- CI must be green before merge.
- Merge via squash or merge commit per team preference; delete branch after merge.

## Traceability chain

```
GitHub Issue â†’ feature branch (from dev) â†’ PR â†’ dev â†’ CI â†’ merge â†’ closes issue â†’ OpenSpec archive
Maintainer: dev â†’ master (release)
```

Every merged change should be recoverable from issue + PR + `openspec/changes/<name>/` history.
